cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.TL, cs.SE, cs.DS

Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category, as the paper discusses a semantics designed for linear logic proofs and its application to programming language semantics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is also likely, as the paper proposes a token-passing abstract machine for implementing evaluation strategies for the lambda calculus. 
- cs.TL (Temporal Logic) is a possibility, as the paper discusses time efficiency of the abstract machine. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is another possibility, as the paper proposes a new abstract machine for implementing evaluation strategies and discusses its efficiency. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses a graph rewriting technique for avoiding duplicated computation.
